import React from "react"; import Card from "react-bootstrap/Card"; import { ListGroup, Container, Row, Col } from "react-bootstrap"; import "../index.css"; import "./Coaching.css"; export default class Coaching extends React.Component { /* cards: - I offer: - online programming - weekly+ checkins - lifitng technique review - nutrition information and effective diet strategies - My philosophy is: - Consistency - Self-efficacy - Find a way to train that you enjoy - Embrace the process - My programming is: - individualized: each program is taylored to your goals and your training history - auto-regulated: we all have good days and bad days––I want you to make the most of both - data-driven: after every week and every block, we look back to make sure what we're doing is working - sustainable: evidence-based injury risk reduction and management so you continue to lift for the rest of your life - Powerlifting, img - Maximize Squat, Bench, Deadlift - Strength and Conditioning, img - Meet exercise guidelines for health - Improve your body composition - Build muscle, lose fat */ render() { const offer = [ "online programming", "weekly+ checkins", "lifting technique review", "nutrition information and strategies", ]; const philosophy = [ "consistency", "self-efficacy", "find a way to train that you enjoy", "embrace the process", ]; const programming = [ "individualized: each program is taylored to your goals and your training history", "auto-regulated: we all have good days and bad days––I want you to make the most of both", "data-driven: after every block, we look back to make sure what we're doing is working", "sustainable: evidence-based injury risk reduction and management so you continue to lift for the rest of your life", ]; const powerlifting = [ "Specalize your squat, bench and deadlift", "Compete", ]; const health = [ "Build muscle", "Lose fat", "Meet (then exceed) exercise guidelines for health", ]; return (
I offer {offer.map((item, i) => ( {item} ))} My philosophy is {philosophy.map((item, i) => ( {item} ))} My programming is {programming.map((item, i) => ( {item} ))} Powerlifting {powerlifting.map((item, i) => ( {item} ))} Strength and Conditioning {health.map((item, i) => ( {item} ))}
); } }
